
[1]quincunx

   QUIN'CUNX, n. [L. composed of quinque, five, and uncia, ounce.]

   In gardening, the quincunx order is a plantation of trees disposed in a
   square, consisting of five trees, one at each corner and a fifth in the
   middle, thus :.:; which order repeated indefinitely, forms a regular
   grove or wood, which viewed by an angle of the square or parallelogram,
   presents equal or parallel alleys.
